node.text: Since Feb 6 I have been plant-based.  I’ve never felt better, have lost 10 pounds (in the first month!) and my LDL cholesterol went from 111 to 81.  I always thought it would be harder than it is. So I wanted to share what a typical weekday looks like. (Btw, if I order from a restaurant or dine outdoors at a restaurant, I Do and will order and eat fish.  I just don’t buy it or cook it at home.) I also believe that there is no one perfect diet for everyone- I think that keto and paleo are great too! When I got my Master’s in Nutrition, I learned a lot about macronutrients.  And hype surrounding certain gimmicky diets... medical and nutritional science literature does show significant health benefits to eating a plant-based diet, and it is significantly better for the environment, but these benefits are offset if a person gains weight by eating lots of empty carbs like bread or pasta etc.  More posts to follow... what are your favorite breakfasts? #plantbased #doctorlifestyle #nutritionistapproved
